#: ../../../gpu-programming/execution-model.md:23
msgid ""
"A kernel launch specifies two things: how many blocks in the grid (the "
"**grid dimensions**) and how many threads in each block (the **block "
"dimensions**). The hardware then groups every 32 consecutive threads into "
"warps automatically -- you never create warps explicitly."
msgstr ""

