#: ../../../gpu-programming/execution-model.md:37
msgid "Thread indexing in cuda-oxide"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/execution-model.md:39
msgid ""
"Inside a kernel, every thread needs to know *which* element it should work "
"on. CUDA provides built-in variables (`threadIdx`, `blockIdx`, `blockDim`, "
"`gridDim`); cuda-oxide wraps these in the `cuda_device::thread` module:"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/execution-model.md:43
msgid ""
"use cuda_device::{kernel, thread, DisjointSlice};\n"
"\n"
"#[kernel]\n"
"pub fn vecadd(a: &[f32], b: &[f32], mut c: DisjointSlice<f32>) {\n"
"    let idx = thread::index_1d();\n"
"    if let Some(c_elem) = c.get_mut(idx) {\n"
"        *c_elem = a[idx.get()] + b[idx.get()];\n"
"    }\n"
"}\n"
msgstr ""

#: ../../../gpu-programming/execution-model.md:55
msgid ""
"`thread::index_1d()` computes `blockIdx.x * blockDim.x + threadIdx.x`. It "
"maps threads to distinct array elements when grid and block Y/Z dimensions "
"are 1. That is the common shape for 1D data-parallel kernels; a `domain = 1` "
"prepared launch proves it."
msgstr ""

